== Open Active Voting

Simple ballot based voting system.

== Installation


1. Install Ruby version 1.9.3-p125

2. Install bundler:
       <tt>gem install bundler</tt>

3. At the command prompt, in the <tt>open-active-democracy</tt> folder:
       <tt>bundle install</tt> (to install Ruby Gem dependencies)

4. Copy and edit the database configuration file:
       cd config
       cp database.yml.dist database.yml
       vi database.yml

5. To create the empty database tables:
       rake db:create
       rake db:schema:load

== Running the tests

1. Change directory to <tt>open-active-democracy</tt> and start the web server:
<tt>cd open-active-democracy; rails server -e test</tt>

2. At a new command prompt, in the <tt>open-active-democracy</tt> folder:
       <tt>rake test</tt> (to run the end to end tests)

== Browsing the test system

1. Open http://localhost:3000/ in your browser